  "timeframe": "1H",
  "market_context": "Silver daily chart shows a sweep of the highs with closure back inside, signalling bearish bias. On the 1-hour chart, price is trading lower from the daily high sweep, with sellside liquidity below as the draw on liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "The first protected high after the sweep is too far away to offer good risk-to-reward. Waiting for a second protected swing to form at a fair value gap allows entry close to invalidation with at least 2R achievable to the downside target.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify daily bearish bias from sweep of daily highs and closure back inside the range.",
    "Step 2: Mark the up-close candle at the high on the 1H chart as the protected swing reference point.",
    "Step 3: Recognize the first protected high offers poor risk-to-reward to the first target and standard deviation projection.",
    "Step 4: Wait for price to retrace into a point of interest (fair value gap) and form a new protected swing via closure through the up-close candle.",
    "Step 5: Sell at the new protected swing with stop placed above the protected high.",
    "Step 6: Target 2R first, then continue toward the first standard deviation projection / sellside liquidity."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade hit 2R target and then continued to the first standard deviation projection.",
  "lessons": "Don't force entries on the first protected swing if risk-to-reward is poor. Allow a new protected swing to form at a point of interest closer to invalidation, giving tight stop and 2R+ to target.",
